## 2. URL FORMATION ŌĆö CRITICAL

### Posts with a `topic` field:
```
https://mirelleinspo.com/blog/{topic}/{slug}
```
Example: `topic: lgbtq`, file `pride-month-nails.md`
ŌåÆ URL: `https://mirelleinspo.com/blog/lgbtq/pride-month-nails`

### Posts WITHOUT a `topic` field:
```
https://mirelleinspo.com/blog/{slug}
```
Example: file `gel-nails-guide.md` with no topic
ŌåÆ URL: `https://mirelleinspo.com/blog/gel-nails-guide`

### Pillar hub pages (topic index):
When a post has `topic` AND `topicalMap.position: pillar`, the topic slug itself becomes a live URL:
```
https://mirelleinspo.com/blog/{topic}
```
This renders a hub page listing all cluster posts under that topic.

### The `slug` in frontmatter = filename without extension (no folder path)
The system derives URLs from `topic` + filename, NOT from the `slug` field directly. The `slug` field just equals the bare filename.

